###############################################################################

Welcome to the Cereus Linux Live system. Two users are available to log in:

	- root:cereus
	- cereus:cereus

The `cereus` user additionally has `sudo(8)` and/or `doas(8)` permissions to run any command
without a password.

To start the TUI installation (for example, on base edition) please type:

    # cereus-installer

To start the GUI installation, open the `Install System` launcher (Calamares) after logging in. And follow the on-screen instructions. 

To install additional software make sure to configure your network interface and then use:

	- xbps-install(1) to install/update packages
	- xbps-query(1) to query for package info

Alternatively, if you chose a GUI edition, you can use OctoXBPS also.
The Void Linux Handbook is also available for offline access in multiple formats, and can be accessed with the `void-docs(1)` utility.

Thanks for using Cereus Linux.

    https://cereuslinuxproject.github.io

###############################################################################
